                        <JFXTextArea layoutX="56.0" layoutY="208.0" prefHeight="279.0" prefWidth="1118.0" style="-fx-text-fill: white;" text="Bierlachs is another form of skat scoring. Here only minus points are written down on the scoreboard and you can’t determine a winner, just a looser. That means if the declarer wins a game thepoints are written down as minus points for the opposition. If the declarer looses a game the pointswill be written down as minus points for the declarer. Usually the players commit to an end score,which can range from 500 to 1000 points. The player who reaches the end score first is the looser ofthe game the others have not lost.Note that this is by no means a classic scoring method and not applicable to the Seeger-System." unFocusColor="PERU">
